  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6811.93 sitting right above the massive -61.9B GEX wall at 6800, dealers are aggressively buying the dip as they're short gamma in this breakout regime. The concentrated negative gamma cluster from 6800-6820 creates a dangerous amplification zone where dealer hedging will accelerate any directional move - if we break below 6800, expect violent selling as dealers chase the move lower. Watch 6840 as the key resistance level where dealers flip to selling pressure, while any bounce attempt faces the gauntlet of negative gamma walls every 5-10 points higher.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price is in a hair-trigger zone where any break of 6800 triggers aggressive selling, but holds above it could spark a sharp rally toward 6840.",
